label: Chronomatric Age
definition: The age of a specimen or related materials that is generated from a dating assay.

label: Chronometric Age ID
definition: An identifier for the set of information associated with a ChronometricAge. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

label: Verbatim Chronometric Age
definition: The verbatim age for a specimen, whether reported by a dating assay, associated references, or legacy information. For example, this could be the conventional radiocarbon age as given in an AMS dating report. This could also be simply what is reported as the age of a specimen in legacy collections data.

label: Verbatim Chronometric Age Conversion Protocol
definition: The method used for converting the verbatimChronometricAge into a chronometric age in years, as captured in the maximumChronometricAge, maximumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem, minimumChronometricAge, and minimumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem fields. For example, calibration of conventional radiocarbon age or the currently accepted age range of a cultural or geological period.

label: Maximum Chronometric Age
definition: Upper limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method. The expected unit for this field is years. This field, if populated, must have an associated maximumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem.

label: Maximum Chronometric Age ReferenceSystem
definition: The reference system associated with the maximumChronometricAge.

label: Minimum Chronometric Age
definition: Lower limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method. The expected unit for this field is years. This field, if populated, must have an associated maximumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem.

label: Minimum Chronometric Age Reference System
definition: The reference system associated with the minimumChronometricAge.

label: Chronometric Age Uncertainty In Years
definition: The temporal uncertainty of the maximumChronometricAge and minimumChronometicAge, in years.

label: Chronometric Age Uncertainty Method
definition: The method used to generate the reported uncertainty calculations.

label: Material Dated
definition: A description of the material on which the chronometricAgeProtocol was actually performed, if known.

label: Material Dated ID
definition: An identifier for the material on which the chronometricAgeProtocol was performed, if applicable.

label: Chronometric Age Protocol
definition: A description of or reference to the methods used to determine the ChronometricAge.

label: Chronometric Age References
definition: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with the ChronometricAge.

label: Chronometric Age Remarks
definition: Notes or comments about the ChronometricAge.

label: Chronometric Age Uncertainty In Years
definition: The temporal uncertainty of the maximumAge and minimumAge, in years.

label: Chronometric Age Uncertainty Method
definition: The method used to generate the reported uncertainty calculations.

label: Maximum Chronometric Age
definition: Upper limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.

label: Maximum Chronometric Age Reference System
definition: The reference system associated with the maximumChronometricAge. For example, BC. It is understood already that this field has the unit of years.

label: Minimum Chronometric Age
definition: Lower limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.

label: Minimum Chronometric Age Reference System
definition: The reference system associated with the minimumChronometricAge. For example, AD. It is understood already that this field has the unit of years.

label: Verbatim Chronometric Age
definition: The verbatim age for a specimen, whether reported by a dating assay, associated references, or legacy information. For example, this could be the conventional radiocarbon age as given in an AMS dating report. This could also be simply what is reported as the age of a specimen in legacy collections data.

label: Verbatim Chronometric Age Conversion Protocol
definition: The method used for converting the verbatimChronometricAge into a chronometric date in years, as captured in the maximumChronometricAge, maximumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem, minimumChronometricAge, and minimumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem fields. For example, calibration of conventional radiocarbon age or the currently accepted age range of a cultural or geological period.

label: Age Uncertainty In Years
definition: The temporal uncertainty of the maximumAge and minimumAge, in years.

label: Maximum Age Reference System
definition: The reference system associated with the maximumAge. For example, BC.

label: Minimum Age Reference System
definition: The reference system associated with the minimumAge. For example, AD.

label: Reported Age
definition: The unconverted output of a dating protocol. For example, the conventional radiocarbon age.

label: Reported Age Conversion Protocol
definition: The method used for converting the reportedAge into a chronometric date, as captured in the maximumAge, maximumAgeUnits, minimumAge, and minimumAgeUnits fields. For example, calibration of conventional radiocarbon age.

label: Chronometric Date
definition: The age of a specimen or related materials that is generated from a dating assay.

label: Age Uncertainty
definition: The assessed temporal uncertainty in the maximum or minimum age estimates, or overall uncertainty for both.

label: Age Uncertainty Method
definition: The method used to generate reported uncertainty calculations.

label: Chronometric Date ID
definition: An identifier for the set of information associated with a ChronometricDate. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.
comments: GUID reference to the combination of information for one ChronometricDate.

label: Chronometric Date Protocol
definition: A description or reference to the methods used to determine the ChronometricDate.

label: Chronometric Date References
definition: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with the ChronometricDate.

label: Chronometric Date Remarks
definition: Notes or comments about the ChronometricDate.

label: Maximum Age
definition: Upper limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.

label: Maximum Age Units
definition: The units associated with the maximumAge.

label: Minimum Age
definition: Lower limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.

label: Minimum Age Units
definition: The units associated with the minimumAge.

label: Material Dated
definition: A description of the material on which the chronometricDateProtocol was actually performed.

label: Material Dated ID
definition: An identifier for the material on which the dating protocol was performed.
